pageContext.claim:
“And you have the other side, even on positive news -- really positive news, like that -- they were like death and un-American. Un-American.
Somebody said, "treasonous." I mean, yeah, I guess, why not?”
pageContext.analysis: Democrats not applauding the president during sections of the State of the Union isn't even close to "treasonous." Instead, it's arguably a demostration of free speech.
